{
  "texts": [
    "We then fine-tuned the language model on the subset of proofs that requires auxiliary constructions, accounting for roughly 9% of the total pretraining data, that is, 9 million proofs, to better focus on its assigned task during proof search.",
    "The performance of ten different solvers on the IMO-AG-30 benchmark is reported in Table 1, of which eight, including AlphaGeometry, are search-based methods.",
    "Besides prompting GPT-4 to produce full proofs in natural language with several rounds of reflections and revisions, we also combine GPT-4 with DD + AR as another baseline to enhance its deduction accuracy.",
    "To achieve this, we use detailed instructions and few-shot examples in the prompt to help GPT-4 successfully interface with DD + AR, providing auxiliary constructions in the correct grammar.",
    "Prompting details of baselines involving GPT-4 is included in the Supplementary Information."
  ]
}